{"change_summary":"No additional code edits were required in this apply-fixes round. The latest review approved the replay-safe milestone task-run lineage changes without amendments, so I left the implementation unchanged and carried forward the existing validation state.","outstanding_risks":["Milestone completion still spans separate lineage, snapshot, and journal files without a cross-file transaction, so a crash can leave snapshot or journal state temporarily behind `task-runs.ndjson` until the same completion is replayed."],"steps":[{"description":"Reviewed the approved validation output for completion round 4 and confirmed there were no follow-up fixes or amendments to apply.","order":0,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Left the existing milestone task-run lineage implementation unchanged because the approved review found no remaining defects requiring code changes.","order":1,"status":"completed"},{"description":"Carried forward the approved validation evidence for formatting, milestone_record tests, and clippy from the latest reviewed implementation.","order":2,"status":"completed"}],"validation_evidence":["Approved review evidence confirms `cargo fmt --all --check` passes with no formatting issues.","Approved review evidence confirms `cargo test --lib contexts::milestone_record` passes with 68 tests.","Approved review evidence confirms `cargo clippy -- -D warnings` passes cleanly."]}